"   <div class=\"ttl\">",
"    C2 pedicle fractures: Hangman's fracture",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 360px; height: 504px; background-image: url(data:image/jpeg;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    Traumatic spondylolysis of C2 (so-called \"hangman's fracture\") is an unstable injury that occurs when the cervicocranium (the skull, atlas, and axis functioning as a unit) is thrown into extreme hyperextension.",
